FORMAT: 1A
HOST: https://www.spotternetwork.org/

# Spotter Network
SpotterNetwork.org is a Not For Profit Organization dedicated to connecting chasers and severe weather enthusiasts. This API serves as a mechanism to share spotters' locations and reports for improved communication within the community.

# Group Authenticate Spotter
Validate a spotter so that your application can perform other calls to the API.

## Log In [/login]
### Retrieve Spotter ID [POST]
+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "username": "xxxxx",
            "password": "xxxxx"
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "success":true,
            "id": "APPLICATION-ID",
            "marker": "PUBLIC-ID",
            "CanReport": true
        }

+ Response 401 (application/json)

        {
          "success": false,
          "errors": [
            "The username or password you entered was incorrect."
          ]
        }
        
+ Response 403 (application/json)

        {
          "success": false,
          "errors": [
            "You have been banned. Reason: Abuser"
          ],
          "id": "APPLICATION-ID",
          "CanReport": false
        }

# Group Spotter Positions
Update a spotter's position or retrieve all spotters' positions that have updated within the last 180 minutes.

## Update Position [/positions/update]
### Update Spotter Position [POST]
+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "id": "APPLICATION-ID",
            "report_at": "YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS",
            "lat": 39.7553101,
            "lon": -105.2330093,
            "elev": 0,
            "mph": 7.5,
            "dir": 328,
            "active": 1,
            "gps": 1
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "success":true
        }

## Get Positions [/positions]
### Get Spotters' Positions [POST]
+ Request Spotters' Positions (application/json)

        {
            "id": "APPLICATION-ID"
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
